Canonical pass/fail contract is tracked in the issue's structured `acceptance_criteria` field. This section is kept in sync for template conformance and planning hygiene.","design":"Deliver correctness tests and operator workflows that validate navigator output against known truth sets and real incidents.","acceptance_criteria":"1. Golden datasets assert timeline and correlation outputs for representative incident classes. - E2e scripts walk through end to end triage from failing lane to narrowed root cause candidate set. - Logging standards ensure every workflow step emits structured, timestamped diagnostics.  5. Comprehensive unit/property tests with deterministic seeds and invariant checks are required for this bead. 6. At least one deterministic end-to-end scenario script validates integrated behavior with replay instructions and artifact capture. 7. Structured logging/metrics must emit trace/run/scenario identifiers, timing, and actionable failure context, and CI must validate schema conformance.","notes":"Priority tuned to P2 until upstream readiness/reporting gates are complete; no reduction in navigator workflow/test scope.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-13T03:05:21.339440541Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-14T04:24:21.193812009Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["alien-pass-2026-02-13","ev-gated"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.7.5.3","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.3.5.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:23:01Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.7.5.3","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.7.5","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:23:01Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.7.5.3","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.7.5.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:23:01Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-mblr.7.6","title":"Automated Regression Bisect and Culprit Isolation","description":"Automate deterministic replay plus commit bisecting for recurring failures to minimize time-to-root-cause.","design":"Automate regression culprit isolation by combining deterministic replay manifests with commit range bisect orchestration.","acceptance_criteria":"1. Replay manifests capture enough context to evaluate pass or fail deterministically at each candidate commit. - Bisect orchestration minimizes reruns and reports confidence with clear culprit metadata. - CI integration can trigger and monitor bisect jobs automatically for qualifying regressions.  Verification contract: completion requires comprehensive unit tests and/or property tests, deterministic end-to-end scenario scripts (harness + replay), and structured logging/metrics validation with trace IDs, timing, counters, and triage artifacts.","notes":"Isolation workflows should prioritize developer feedback speed while preserving reproducibility guarantees.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-13T03:05:21.429730391Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-14T04:31:14.514734522Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.7.6","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.7","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:23:01Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
