 {"id":"bd-mblr.7.6.2","title":"Deterministic bisect orchestrator","description":"Implement orchestrator that replays failure across commit range and identifies first bad change deterministically.

## Acceptance Criteria
Canonical pass/fail contract is tracked in the issue's structured `acceptance_criteria` field. This section is kept in sync for template conformance and planning hygiene.","design":"Implement deterministic bisect orchestrator that executes replay manifests across commit ranges with robust retry and caching logic.","acceptance_criteria":"1. Orchestrator supports binary search style commit selection with resumable state. - Execution logs include commit hash, evaluator result, runtime, and artifact pointers for each step. - Integration tests validate correctness on synthetic histories with injected flaky and deterministic failures.  5. Comprehensive unit/property tests with deterministic seeds and invariant checks are required for this bead. 6. At least one deterministic end-to-end scenario script validates integrated behavior with replay instructions and artifact capture. 7. Structured logging/metrics must emit trace/run/scenario identifiers, timing, and actionable failure context, and CI must validate schema conformance.","notes":"When flakiness is detected, mark result uncertain and escalate instead of fabricating deterministic verdicts.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-13T03:05:21.611519286Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-14T00:37:09.174822658Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["alien-pass-2026-02-13","ev-gated"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.7.6.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.7.6","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:23:01Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.7.6.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.7.6.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:23:01Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-mblr.7.6.3","title":"CI and operator hooks for auto-bisect","description":"Add trigger policy for automatic bisect on recurrent failures and publish result artifacts for engineers.

## Acceptance Criteria
Canonical pass/fail contract is tracked in the issue's structured `acceptance_criteria` field. This section is kept in sync for template conformance and planning hygiene.","design":"Wire auto bisect triggers into CI and provide operator controls for scope, priority, cancellation, and result publication.","acceptance_criteria":"1. CI trigger policy routes eligible regressions into bisect with bounded concurrency controls. - Result summaries include likely culprit commit range, confidence level, and linked replay artifacts. - E2e workflow tests cover success, uncertainty, cancellation, and timeout paths.  5. Comprehensive unit/property tests with deterministic seeds and invariant checks are required for this bead. 6. At least one deterministic end-to-end scenario script validates integrated behavior with replay instructions and artifact capture. 7. Structured logging/metrics must emit trace/run/scenario identifiers, timing, and actionable failure context, and CI must validate schema conformance.","notes":"Priority tuned to P2 so immediate focus stays on prerequisite bisect/manifest gates; CI/operator hook feature set remains intact.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-13T03:05:21.697393069Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-14T04:24:20.867118736Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["alien-pass-2026-02-13","ev-gated"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.7.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.3.2.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:23:01Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.7.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.7.6","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:23:01Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.7.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.7.6.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:23:01Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-mblr.7.7","title":"Resource Leak Budgets and Gates","description":"Add leak observability and budget enforcement for fds/memory/tempfiles/side artifacts across unit and e2e lanes.","design":"Introduce resource telemetry, leak budgets, and gating so long run quality remains stable and regressions are caught before user impact.","acceptance_criteria":"- Resource telemetry covers memory, file descriptors, threads, and temp storage growth across test lanes.
- Leak budgets define threshold policies with severity levels and ownership mapping.
